theorem
Th60: (for L being domRing holds (for x being (Element of L) holds (for n being (Element of ( NAT )) holds ( degree ( BRoots ( <% ( - x ),( 1. L ) %> `^ n ) ) ) = n)))
proof
let L being domRing;
let x being (Element of L);
set r = <% ( - x ),( 1. L ) %>;
defpred P[ (Element of ( NAT )) ]
 means
( degree ( BRoots ( r `^ $1 ) ) ) = $1;
A1: (for n being (Element of ( NAT )) holds (P[ n ] implies P[ ( n + 1 ) ]))
proof
let n being (Element of ( NAT ));
assume that
A2: P[ n ];
( r `^ ( n + 1 ) ) = ( ( r `^ n ) *' r ) by POLYNOM5:19;
then A3: ( degree ( BRoots ( r `^ ( n + 1 ) ) ) ) = ( ( degree ( BRoots ( r `^ n ) ) ) + ( degree ( BRoots r ) ) ) by Lm2
.= ( n + ( degree ( ({ x },1) -bag ) ) ) by A2,CKB76:1;
( card { x } ) = 1 by CARD_1:30;
hence thesis by A3,CKB23:1;
end;
(( len ( 1_. L ) ) = 1 & ( r `^ ( 0 ) ) = ( 1_. L )) by POLYNOM4:4,POLYNOM5:15;
then A4: P[ ( 0 ) ] by CKB79:1;
thus (for n being (Element of ( NAT )) holds P[ n ]) from NAT_1:sch 1(A4,A1);
end;
